    "For example, researchers found that software developers and engineering students did not change their established ways of working even when a code of ethics was widely available and recommended [15].Rising to the challenge of designing and deploying ethical AI to serve healthcare is essential.",
    "Still, many questions remain regarding the characteristics and processes that would support AI's ethical development and implementation.",
    "Most researchers have focused on \"consumer research\" on the conditions for people to accept the usage of AI [19].",
    "In two recently published systematic reviews of empirical research available for AI in healthcare, most studies explored the knowledge and attitudes towards AI or factors contributing to stakeholders' acceptance or adoption [20,21].",
    "However, how AI is developed may affect its acceptance by stakeholders or usage."
